table-0333-240.caption: Episodes
data: The Village Fete 1993. Simmi joins a dating agency. A new village bobby appears in the village.
Simmi goes on first date at agency. Pam Holmes plans parachute jump
Terry Cox planning to win cup at Fete. Preparations for the fete start
Pam Holmes makes parachute jump. Bentley Fete opens. Cow Pat lottery with Claire the Coe. Simmi does face painting at fete.
Hop pickers arrive. Simmi meets John on second data at fete - but it's the last. Alan Wheatley has doubts about future of the village stores.
Alan Wheatley plans to cut the stores in half. Simmi searches the dating agency again. The by-pass work starts.
The Star pub changes gets a new landlord. Elvis (Dave the Plumber) looks at Pinkie's plumbing.
Pinkie lies in wait for burglars at Bentley stores. The threat to local business by the new bypass. Pinkie shops for baby clothes.
Debbie Salmon is pregnant. The pheasant shoot.
Tony wants to dig gravel from his land to build a by-pass, but neighbour and brother-in-law, Jumbo objects.
The Balloon flight. Chris Holmes plans his marriage – but to Sarah a 'townie'
Dave the Plumber announces marriage to Dee. Jumbo plans action against gravel extraction to build by-pass.
The girl with no belly button.
Simmi's new boyfriend has a surprise for Simmi. Les moving from Germany to Bentley to set up new business. Elvis (Dave the Plumber) sings.
Will Les propose? Simmi's mum arrives from Switzerland to meet Les. Simmi and Les view new offices on Bentley Industrial Estate. New police woman arrives in Bentley.
WPC Woodcock arrives. Les and Simmi's software arrives and move into new offices. Chris Holmes's stag night
Preparations for Froyle pantomime – with WPC Sue Woodcock as Mother Goose
Simmi and Les employ new staff, but no money to pay wages. Tony Holmes goes on fox hunt. Mary at The Bull pub needs staff. Chris Holmes's wedding preparations in Wales.
Chris and Sarah's wedding in Wales. Simmi and Les prepare for computer fair at Olympia, London.
Simmi and Les finally sell software at Olympia. Final rehearsal for Mother Goose. WPC Sue Woodcock gets bad news from Australia.
WPC Sue Woodcock mother has heart attack in Australia. Mother Goose performs. Farmer Colin Meatyard announces end of his marriage. James Campbell the new vicar announced.
Simmi and Les discuss the effects of contraception – and vasectomy. Colin Meatyard to sell dairy herd to settle his divorce. Will the bypass mean the end of Bentley stores?
Les decides to have vasectomy. Bentley Bypass opens.
Les has the vasectomy. Campaigns for local election candidates starts. Preparations for 100th villager fete starts.
Simmi rushes to Switzerland to see her ill father. Local elections. Colin finds Lorraine in "lonely hearts" in Farmers Weekly.
Election results. Simmi returns from Switzerland after her father dies. Marion explains about dyslexic children.
Nicholas Parsons opens 100th Bentley fete. Marion to go to House of Lords to appeal against dyslexia laws. Thefts from allotments.
Marion wins appeal at House of Lords re dyslexia laws and celebrates. Simmi's mum comes to stay. Tony wins election.
WPC Sue Woodcock can't raise air fare to Australia. Simmi and Les expand office. Does Colin need to sell farm to pay ex-wife?
Sue arrives in Australia to visit dying mother. Peter Blackman is new taxi driver in village. Simmi and Les take staff to Chequers pub. CSA chases Les.
Letter from CSA for Les upsets Simmi. Sue asks why did her mother abandon her and move to Australia. Sarah announces that she will not give up Jon in London.
Mark Christmas, on morale high due to Lords judgement gets new girlfriend. Star landlord to leave.
Sue returns from Australia Nicky wants to be new landlord of Star pub. Marion meets Marks new girlfriend. Les divorce delayed. Tony Holmes has a weight problem.
Bob Wilson and Nicky Meatyard are new landlord of the Star. Will Adrian the PI sponsor the Bentley football team. Bentley loses 6-2 leaving sponsorship is in doubt.
Tony Holmes is diabetic. Sue investigates local signs being stolen. Star opens with Nicky and Bob as landlords.
Les has problems collecting from bad debtors. Simmi has car crash and has to wear neck brace. Chequers get new French chef. Lorraine plans party for Colin.
Les gets response from CSA. Colin has birthday party. Bentley cook book launched.
Great crested newt found in the pond - but this is a problem for the ducks.
Duck & Newt story gets into national press. Cook book content continues to grow.
Is the Chequers haunted? Ducks get a reprieve. Les arranges printing of the Bentley cook book Tony Holmes's Sarah is pregnant.
Cook book sales go well. Medium arrives at the Chequers.
Simmi and Les decide to renovate their cottage, but wants ex-husband to do the work. Dave the Plumber has an accident.
Simmi's ex Dick starts work on the cottage. Dave the Plumber goes to police station to explain what happened on stage.
Les is critical about work by Dick at the cottage. Dave visits his solicitor about assault incident. Terry persuades Joan to go to the races. Dave sings at village show.
Sue sings at village show. Andrew narrates at show.
Lorraine wants to join the police force. Huge ugly surgery sign appears. Les and Simmi plan to expand the software business
Lorraine takes police exam. Joan taken to hospital. Petition to remove ugly village road sign.
Lorraine fails police entrance exam. Alan makes plans for the shop. Bentley road sign is removed.
PC Sue Woodcock plans her retirement from police force. Simmi and Les announce their wedding plans. Les proposes on holiday in Turkey.

Penny makes her will. Bentley fete opens. Les converting part of his office in the industrial estate for Simmi new salon. Sue in the stocks. Simmi and Les prepare their wedding list. Penny goes gliding.
Tony in hospital. Andrew inspects sea cadets. Simmi and Les in-laws meet. Sue and Lorraine discuss strange lights in the sky. UFO in Hampshire?
Sue believes lights are a UFO. Simmi's mum has doubts about wedding. Peter Blackman want to run the pub. Simmi and Les design their engagement ring. More UFOs.
Peter Blackman is the new landlord of The Star. Sue plans her farewell party. Simmi listens to an old clairvoyants tape recording. Les picks up engagement ring. Sue has her party at The Star.
Simmi and Les disagree about wedding. Sue moves out. WPC Sarah Wilcox comes to village. Dave wants to go to Gracelands.
WPC Wilcox arrests someone for slashing tyres in village. Peter plans B&B in Bentley at The Star. Lorraine inherits some money and wants to invest in The Star pub.
Dave is scared of flying to USA. Les and Simmi have their engagement dinner. Simmi plans to expand her salon.
Catherine passes her driving test. The Star gets its first B&B customer. Dave goes on his fear of flying course at Heathrow.
Simmi records her pilot radio show - but it can't be edited. WPC Sarah issues speeding tickets in Bentley.
Simmi's radio show gets rejected. Sue Woodcock opens the village fete. Simmi hears her mum has cancer and returns home to Switzerland. Tony and Jumbo go to paint ball range.
Sarah gets married. Andrew gets upset about plan to build 100 homes in Bentley. Peter starts to receive nuisance calls. Simmi returns home to Bentley after her mum has operation.
Hilda is upset by careless dogs and their owners fouling the footbaths. Campaign against new development continues. WPC Kedge identifies the nuisance calls to Peter.
Will Tony sell land for development? Village pond needs cleaning, but there are no volunteers.
The dog fouling officer starts fining offenders. Dee needs a hysterectomy. Community service offenders clean pond. Les plans Simmi 40th birthday to.....
Tony collects his restored Morris Minor. Dee's operation is a success. Simmi and Les set off on surprise trip - 1st class.
Les takes Simmi to Paris for 40th birthday, but Simmi just wast to go shopping. Les has problems with his French. Les proposes to Simmi. Colin sells his dairy herd.
Colins language puts off buyers. Alan seeks loan from bank to improve the village stores. Tony and Jumbo have a car race.
Alan has meeting with bank manager and gets loan. The great car race continues.
Tony wins the great car race. Alans starts to split his shop into two – but there are delays. Simmi and Les argue about details of their marriage plans.
Les and Simmi choose outfit for the wedding - but Les must lose weight. Terry and Joan have their 50th wedding anniversary party.
Les continues his diet and takes up exercising. Peter starts clamping non patrons in the pub car park. Dave fails to get on Stars in their Eyes. Mary works on Simmi's wedding dress
Les loses enough weight to get married. Jumbo discovers a strange plant in garden - is it legal? Dave performs as Elvis at The Star pub. Colin parks his tractor in pub car park.
Les and Simmi check out wedding venues and then collects Simmi's mum from airport. As Simmi invites her ex-husband, Les invites his ex-wife Melanie to Wedding. WPC Sarah announces she is pregnant.
The Star loses customers to The Chequers. Andrew and Mary prepare surprise for Hilda's 80th. Les goes to his quiet stag night while Simmi has a wild hen night.
Simmi has a hangover from the hen night. Hilda's surprise party with a "This is Your Life" presentation.
Simmi is nervous prior to the wedding, while Les has to work late. Peter upgrades the facilities at The Star.
Hop picking. Captain Thompson and Mary continue to edit their Bentley book. Pinkie, the Star pub landlord, receives hate mail. Simmi and Les decide on future of the software business.
Les gets overwhelming interest at exhibition. Pinkie suspects everyone as source of poison-pen letter. Captain Thompson completes his Official History of Bentley book. Mary remembers times past.

Then Olaf held a speech out in the farm, he went up unto a great rock lying near the pig sty. Olaf spoke, and in his speech he said he would reward any man richly who could harm Hákon Earl. The Earl and Kark heard this speech. They had light where they lay. The Earl said: "Why are you so pale, yet sometimes black as dirt? It is not so that you wish to harm me?" "No," says Kark. "We were born on the same night," says the Earl. "Close will also our deaths be."
